<h2>Property Distribution</h2>
<p>The State of Florida is an equitable property distribution state. This means that all assets acquired during the
    marriage, regardless of who actually purchased or gifted the asset, will be subject to equal distribution. The
    family court will split the marital assets as close to 50-50 as possible during the divorce proceedings. </p>
<h2>Child Custody</h2>
<p>Although one parent may be designated as a primary custodian, Florida requires both parents to share equally in the
    financial, health, education, and emotional well-being of raising their minor child or children.</p>
<p>During a divorce, both parents will be required to submit an acceptable Parental Timesharing Agreement to the court,
    or the judge may define a plan for them that will become a lawful order.</p>
